main event: Two unidentified lights, one blue and one green/yellow, were sighted by FAA personnel at the FAA airport in Yakutat, Alaska.
interesting points: The blue light was observed moving from the zenith towards the south at an altitude of 20,000 feet.
The green/yellow light was observed moving from west to southeast at an altitude of 12,000 feet.
The sighting was evaluated as possibly being a meteor or a comet.
Weather conditions at the time included good visibility, scattered clouds, and normal temperature gradient except for a shallow inversion between 7,700 and 8,200 feet.
The observers were identified as having excellent reliability, including a weather bureau employee and an FAA employee.
